Installation Guide for PHP Job Seeker 2
========================================

Prerequisites
-------------

- Apache httpd (or similar web server) with PHP module
- PHP 5.6 or later (tested with PHP 8.4)
- MySQL 5.6 or later (tested with MySQL 8.4)
- PHP mysqli extension

In your PHP configuration (/etc/php.ini on Unix), set the timezone. For example,
if you're in the Central US timezone:

    date.timezone = America/Chicago

Installation Steps
------------------

1) Clone the repository into your web server's document root:

    git clone git@github.com:kbcmdba/pjs2.git /var/www/html/pjs2

2) Create the MySQL database and application user:

    mysql -e "CREATE DATABASE pjs2;"
    mysql -e "CREATE USER 'pjs2_app'@'127.0.0.1' IDENTIFIED BY 'YourPasswordHere';"
    mysql -e "GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON pjs2.* TO 'pjs2_app'@'127.0.0.1';"
    mysql -e "FLUSH PRIVILEGES;"

3) Copy config_sample.xml to config.xml and update it with your settings:

    cp config_sample.xml config.xml

   Required settings in config.xml:
   - dbHost, dbPort, dbName, dbUser, dbPass: your MySQL connection details
   - userId, userPassword: credentials for the PJS2 web interface
   - timeZone: your local timezone (e.g., America/Chicago)

4) Initialize the database by visiting resetDb.php in your browser or running:

    php-cgi resetDb.php

   This creates all tables, triggers, and seed data.

MySQL 8 Notes
-------------

MySQL 8 introduced two changes that affect installation:

a) GRANT ALL ON dbname.* no longer implicitly allows creating the database.
   You must create the database (step 2 above) before the application user
   can use it.

b) If binary logging is enabled, you must allow the application user to
   create triggers:

    mysql -e "SET GLOBAL log_bin_trust_function_creators = 1;"

   To make this persistent across MySQL restarts, add to your MySQL
   configuration (e.g., /etc/my.cnf or /etc/my.cnf.d/*.cnf):

    [mysqld]
    log_bin_trust_function_creators = 1

   Run this before step 4 (resetDb.php), or trigger creation will fail.
